This is README file for Algorithm PA#1
Author: B11901110 Syuan-Ji Chen
Date: 2024-10-05
=====
SYNOPSIS:

NTU_sort -[IS|MS|BMS|QS|RQS|HS] <input_file_name> <output_file_name>

This program supports six different sorting methods: insertion sort, merge sort, 
bottom-up merge sort, quick sort, randomized quick sort and heap sort.
=====
DIRECTORY:

bin/	  executable binary
doc/	  reports
inputs/   input data (unsorted)
outputs/  output result (sorted)
lib/	  library
src/ 	  source C++ codes
utility/  checker
======
HOW TO COMPILE:

	Under the root directory of this PA, simply type
	make
======
HOW TO RUN:

	cd bin/
	./bin/NTU_sort -[IS|MS|BMS|QS|RQS|HS] <input_file_name> <output_file_name>
	For example,
	under <student_id>_pa1
	./bin/NTU_sort -MS inputs/1000.case1.in outputs/1000.case1.out
======
HOW TO VERIFY RESULT

    cd utility/
    ./PA1_Result_Checker <input_file_name> <result_file_name>
	For example,
	under <student_id>_pa1
	./utility/PA1_Result_Checker ./inputs/5.case1.in ./outputs/5.case1.out
======
OTHER NOTICE:
